  "elapsed_s": 2.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When I am asked this question, I would say there was one event worth to survive, maybe even two.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But the first one didn't last long, only 50 years.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The partition of Germany was won and the regaining-- [CRYING] I'm even moved now by the idea, at the time, of our homeland of Israel in 1948-- was the second one and the main one, which was worthwhile to surviving for.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When they said, 'Never again,' [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I know what they mean.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My country, right or wrong-- my country.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And if people sometimes say-- when you hear sometimes, deeds which were not, perhaps, to the modern standard of what one should or should not do, don't forget they only do it there in revenge.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was done to them first, not by the Germans, in this case-- by the Arabs.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Shalom.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
